  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">α</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">S</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">L</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">σ</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">S</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">S</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">E</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 </sub>
 <italic class="italic">l</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">l</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">e</italic>
 </sub>, and 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">G</italic>
 </sub> are surface albedo, downward shortwave radiation, downward longwave radiation, the Stefan–Boltzmann constant, surface temperature in Kelvin, sensible heat flux, latent heat flux, latent heat for evaporation of water or ice, and conductive heat flux into glacier ice, respectively.
